fields.title: THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS
fields.review: Sleek and shiny on the surface, The Fast and the Furious recalls those cheesy teenage exploitation flicks of the 1950s.

fields.title: 2 FAST 2 FURIOUS
fields.review: Beautiful people and beautiful cars in a movie that won't tax the brain cells.

fields.title: FAST & FURIOUS
fields.review: While Fast and Furious features the requisite action and stunts, the filmmakers have failed to provide a competent story or compelling characters.

fields.title: FAST FIVE
fields.review: Sleek, loud, and over the top, Fast Five proudly embraces its brainless action thrills and injects new life into the franchise.

fields.title: FAST & FURIOUS 6
fields.review: With high-octane humor and terrific action scenes, Fast & Furious 6 builds upon the winning blockbuster formula that made Fast 5 a critical and commercial success.

fields.title: THE FAST AND THE FURIOUS: TOKYO DRIFT
fields.review: Eye-popping driving sequences coupled with a limp story and flat performances make this Drift a disappointing follow-up to previous Fast and Furious installments.

fields.title: FURIOUS 7
fields.review: Serving up a fresh round of over-the-top thrills while adding unexpected dramatic heft, Furious 7 keeps the franchise moving in more ways than one.

fields.title: THE FATE OF THE FURIOUS
fields.review: The Fate of the Furious opens a new chapter in the franchise, fueled by the same infectious cast chemistry and over-the-top action fans have come to expect.

fields.title: FAST & FURIOUS PRESENTS: HOBBS & SHAW
fields.review: Hobbs & Shaw doesn't rev as high as the franchise's best installments, but gets decent mileage out of its well-matched stars and over-the-top action sequences.

fields.title: F9 THE FAST SAGA
fields.review: F9 sends the franchise hurtling further over the top than ever, but director Justin Lin's knack for preposterous set pieces keeps the action humming.
